prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "States VerifyCard and OutOfService cannot be redefined",
      "evidence_quote": "All other States can be redefined."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The VerifyTransaction to ReleaseCard Transition cannot be redefined",
      "evidence_quote": "The VerifyTransaction to ReleaseCard Transition has also been specified as final,"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Users can enter a desired amount in the State EnterAmount",
      "evidence_quote": "so that users can enter a desired amount"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Two new Transitions are added, one into and one out of the new State EnterAmount",
      "evidence_quote": "two new Transitions, one into and one out of the new State."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The State SelectedAmount is redefined to act as the source or target for a new Transition",
      "evidence_quote": "The State SelectedAmount and the FinalState from ReadAmount are redefined in order to act as"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The State VerifyTransaction is redefined to act as the source of a new Transition with EnterAmount as its target",
      "evidence_quote": "In addition, the State VerifyTransaction is redefined in order to act as the source of a new Transition."
    }
  ]
}

llm_response:
Here is the rewritten JSON:

{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "States VerifyCard and OutOfService cannot be redefined",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall not redefine States VerifyCard and OutOfService."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "The VerifyTransaction to ReleaseCard Transition cannot be redefined",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall not redefine the VerifyTransaction to ReleaseCard Transition."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Users can enter a desired amount in the State EnterAmount",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow users to enter a desired amount in the State EnterAmount."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Two new Transitions are added, one into and one out of the new State EnterAmount",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall add two new Transitions, one into and one out of the new State EnterAmount."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "The State SelectedAmount is redefined to act as the source or target for a new Transition",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall redefine the State SelectedAmount to act as the source or target for a new Transition."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "The State VerifyTransaction is redefined to act as the source of a new Transition with EnterAmount as its target",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall redefine the State VerifyTransaction to act as the source of a new Transition with EnterAmount as its target."
    }
  ]
}
